I’m not the one to ever play the victim or come off weak but yesterday was a real shocker and eye opener. No matter how good you are or good things you do, there’s always going to be someone to hate or want to do harm to you. 

I live in a 24 hour guard gated community and despite all of our safety measures 3 dudes still had the balls to somehow try to invade my house. As they were in my backyard looking around, thank god I was coming downstairs to get food. 

I don’t know what it was but when that happen they took off after. Whether I was targeted or it was by random, it’s still something that fucked with my nerves and my families. Obviously now myself and the whole neighborhood have taken more precautious bc this could have been way worse. 

I just also wanted to make everyone aware if you haven’t that it’s the Wild Wild West out there and these things are happening more and more often. Please be safe and cautious. If you recognize any of these dudes, please dm. Thank you.

The only thing that scared me about the Ironman was swimming. 6 months ago I could barely swim, I hired a coach and woke up at the crack of dawn and put countless hours at the la fitness swimming laps.

I’m still far from a great swimmer but shit I didn’t drown and made the 1.2 mile swim. The last 6 months of training for @ironmantri has been so intense, 2-3 hours a day minimum of either running, swimming or biking or sometimes all together.

I just wanted to thank everyone that helped with this journey. Shit was fun but man I’m glad I got that shit done. Take it from me as well, you’re never too old to do anything. It’s either you do it or you make excuses not to. 

1.2  mile 🏊
56 mile 🚴
13.1 mile 🏃
Mission complete✅

I’ve been asked quite frequently what the biggest motivation to my success was. She was it. My daughter Jordyn… At 31 years old, I became responsible for another human being, to physically and financially make sure she was taken care of… Shit was scary af to process at first because during that time as a sales rep, I was paid on commission base. I never knew what my next check would look like. There was never a guaranteed amount I’d be bringing home and now I’m responsible for her as well?⁣
 ⁣
I still remember that time like it was yesterday —barely in my first year of business and getting my first office in downtown Santa Ana. I was so fucken proud of my showroom… It was the first time I owned anything that I could call mine. a 650 sq ft office for $750/month. That was the very moment I finally felt like I made it.⁣
 ⁣
I’ve come a long way and looking at some of these photos… Especially this one, exactly a decade ago with J at 3 months old in the DTSA office, puts into perspective how far you can go by just really hustling… Fast forward now at 41 years old... I’m humbled af because I have these photos and memories to look back on to remind me that shit don’t happen overnight and of course my favorite saying I used to tell my friends “Ferraris aint free.” #TBT

Ran my first half marathon this time last year, and it really changed my outlook on health and taking care of my body. I got addicted to pushing myself physically and mentally, just like everything else I do. I do NOT half ass anything. I dove into endurance training and learned about so much — zone training, nutrition, breathing techniques and most importantly, RECOVERY. I can’t stress this enough, you’re only going to improve and get better at running, biking and/or swimming based on how fast your body RECOVERS to go on to the next training session.⁣
 ⁣
In 10 months, I ran 3 half marathons and even finished 3rd place in one with times of (1:58, PR 1:41, 1:45) 1 full marathon (3:58) and finished an Ironman 70.3. At 41 years old, the goal wasn’t to just try and finish… I was out there really lapping guys way younger than me. That’s the competitor in me… Don’t let anyone tell you you’re too old to do anything bc fuck that…an old dog can learn new tricks. #themarathoncontinues

Thank you Business Concepts for covering our story. The garment industry isn’t new to me. This wasn’t something I just “fell” into. My mother made her living in the fashion industry as part of the supply chain as a “sewer” who sewed together garments. Beginning at 4 years old, I spent my childhood literally hanging out in a sweatshop. 

At an early age I understood exactly what went on in the PRODUCTION side of apparel. From being the son of a factory worker who didn’t speak any English, getting paid 20 cents per garment, to being an important part of the industry… You can say my success now is pretty much full circle and I couldn’t be more blessed.

To buy the magazine…the link is in my bio! #santaanaboyz #theleverage

What we specialize in, some people in the fashion industry call a “dying breed.” I have peers and friends that ask me why I’m still so invested on wholesale when I can just ramp up my SEO, pay for ads and focus on DTC. Cut out the middle man and increase margins. My answer is this, I’m ok with still being the unicorn and doing old school business the way it should be done… FACE TO FACE.
 
I still believe that people do business with people. I don’t rely on catchy content, Google Analytics or paid ads to stay in business. To be honest, nothing is more satisfying than to see your product all over the world in various stores.
 
So for that… It’s been a minute since I’ve done any collection or line showings; but, I’m coming out of retirement for this show. The best sales rep this industry has ever seen is back… Yes motherfucker I said it, THE BEST.
 
If you’re trying to personally have me show you our collections, please DM me or email Sales@the-leverage.com for an appointment to see some of the collections we’re showing in Vegas. See you there. #saleslife

I started the @leveragebasketballacademy back in 2020 primarily just to create a program that focused on providing skills, training, and the basic fundamentals of the game for my kids and a handful of their 5-7 year old friends at the time. As the program grew and the kids got older, we started to play in scrimmages, tournaments, and various leagues. My vision was to always have my kids play as competitively as possible in AAU/club/travel ball. 

Having a daughter and putting a girls team together was very tough because there weren’t many girls her age playing. I was actually lucky enough to find an amazing girls program coached by one of the best high school coaches in Orange County with 20+ years of experience. Coach Pablo Martinez is the varsity head coach at Pacifica Christian and rans @socalbulldogsbasketballacademy. Watching how he ran that club program made me very excited to come together and merge our academies, putting together a club program we call Leverage Bulldogs. 

Last weekend we played our first tournament as a club program together, combing players from Leverage Basketball Academy and SoCal Bulldogs Academy to compete in the West Coast Elite tournament. We entered 4 teams into 3 divisions, ending up with 2 of our teams playing against each other in the finals. The girls won the 9U, and our 14U team walked away with first place in the gold division. 

My and Coach Pablo’s goals are to build one of the best and most competitive programs in our area, and most importantly… compete and win. If you’re looking for an academy or club program that’s not a cash grab, actually cares about winning and putting out the best product, and you want to get the most out of your kids, we’d love to have your player in one of our programs.
I did that! 2nd @ironmantri in the books. 97 degrees in the desert of Tempe, Arizona ✅
My favorite holiday of all holidays. #Halloween🚶🚶🚶🌲🌴🌳

Also the 10u and 14u teams all got ranked in the top 15 in their division as well. Let’s keep 📈📈📈📈! 

Lastly thanks to all my homies you know who you are that sponsored some of tournaments! You sponsored some hard working kids. Thank you again!  @leveragebasketballacademy

This year, I found myself taking a backseat to my kids, and I love it. I had the opportunity to be a cheerleader, fan, and coach to my kids. I watched them hit their first 3, play lockdown d, cross up kids, and get 🪣’s on the court. Witnessing the progress of my kids was worth every second I spent running the program, taking them to practice, coaching the team, and dedicating weekends to tournaments.

I also managed to find some time for personal training. I completed a few Ironman events, ran some marathons, and got in decent shape. Leading by example, that’s what I did. Oh yeah, I still ran a pretty solid business that accomplished a lot of cool things, but as of now, I let that speak for itself. I’m just glad I’m still here—healthy, happy, and still in business. I hope 2023 was good for y’all because in 2024, it’s still always going to be the same old me.

We have officially merged with @socalbulldogs as of this year and will be practicing at The Village Bible Church in Garden Grove. Our program will be lead by owner/founder and also head coach of Pacifica Christian’s girls varsity team Pablo Martinez. 

We are committed to building a strong base of fundamental skills and teaching high basketball iq for all our kids in the program. If you are a parent that would want training for your kids please dm or email us. 

As the program grows. We are looking to add kids to our club program to play and compete in the best tournaments locally. Try outs are next week! Please dm for any questions.
